<h2>Starting a Business in Pennsylvania</h2>
<p>Choosing the right business structure is one of the most important decisions you'll make as an entrepreneur. The entity you select affects your personal liability, tax obligations, management flexibility, and ability to raise capital.</p>
<p>At Ament Law Group, we provide legal guidance in the planning and formation of business entities, helping you select and establish the structure that best fits your goals.</p>
<h2>Business Entity Types</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Limited Liability Company (LLC)</strong> — Combines liability protection with tax flexibility. The most popular choice for small businesses in Pennsylvania.</li>
    <li><strong>Corporation (S-Corp or C-Corp)</strong> — Provides strong liability protection and is well-suited for businesses seeking investors or planning to go public.</li>
    <li><strong>Partnership (General or Limited)</strong> — Appropriate for businesses with two or more owners who want to share management and profits.</li>
    <li><strong>Sole Proprietorship</strong> — The simplest structure, though it offers no personal liability protection.</li>
</ul>
